 {"id":"charmed_rust-5x5.1.6","title":"Implement ConformanceTest Trait and Runner","description":"# Implement ConformanceTest Trait and Runner

## Purpose
Create the trait that all conformance tests implement, plus a runner that discovers and executes tests.

## Requirements

### Test Trait
```rust
pub trait ConformanceTest: Send + Sync {
    /// Human-readable test name
    fn name(&self) -> &str;

    /// Which crate this tests
    fn crate_name(&self) -> &str;

    /// Test category
    fn category(&self) -> TestCategory;

    /// Run the test
    fn run(&self, ctx: &mut TestContext) -> TestResult;

    /// Optional benchmark (default: None)
    fn benchmark(&self, ctx: &mut BenchContext) -> Option<BenchResult> {
        None
    }

    /// Dependencies on other tests
    fn dependencies(&self) -> Vec<&str> {
        vec![]
    }
}

#[derive(Clone, Copy)]
pub enum TestCategory {
    Unit,
    Integration,
    EdgeCase,
    Performance,
}
```

### Test Registry
```rust
pub struct TestRegistry {
    tests: HashMap<String, Box<dyn ConformanceTest>>,
}

impl TestRegistry {
    pub fn new() -> Self;

    /// Register a test
    pub fn register<T: ConformanceTest + 'static>(&mut self, test: T);

    /// Get all tests for a crate
    pub fn tests_for_crate(&self, crate_name: &str) -> Vec<&dyn ConformanceTest>;

    /// Get tests by category
    pub fn tests_by_category(&self, category: TestCategory) -> Vec<&dyn ConformanceTest>;

    /// Get all tests
    pub fn all_tests(&self) -> Vec<&dyn ConformanceTest>;
}
```

### Test Runner
```rust
pub struct TestRunner {
    registry: TestRegistry,
    fixtures: FixtureLoader,
    config: RunnerConfig,
}

pub struct RunnerConfig {
    pub parallel: bool,
    pub filter: Option<String>,
    pub categories: Vec<TestCategory>,
    pub benchmarks: bool,
    pub verbose: bool,
}

pub struct RunResults {
    pub tests: Vec<TestResult>,
    pub benchmarks: Vec<BenchResult>,
    pub total_duration: Duration,
}

impl TestRunner {
    pub fn new(registry: TestRegistry, fixtures: FixtureLoader) -> Self;

    /// Run all registered tests
    pub fn run_all(&self) -> RunResults;

    /// Run tests for specific crate
    pub fn run_crate(&self, crate_name: &str) -> RunResults;

    /// Run tests matching filter
    pub fn run_filtered(&self, filter: &str) -> RunResults;
}
```

### Usage Pattern
```rust
// Define a conformance test
struct RedTextTest;

impl ConformanceTest for RedTextTest {
    fn name(&self) -> &str { "render_red_text" }
    fn crate_name(&self) -> &str { "lipgloss" }
    fn category(&self) -> TestCategory { TestCategory::Unit }

    fn run(&self, ctx: &mut TestContext) -> TestResult {
        let style = Style::new().foreground(Color::Red);
        let input = "Hello";

        ctx.log_input("text", &input);

        let expected = ctx.fixture::<String>("lipgloss/red_text")?;
        let actual = style.render(input);

        ctx.assert_ansi_eq(&expected, &actual);
        ctx.finish()
    }

    fn benchmark(&self, ctx: &mut BenchContext) -> Option<BenchResult> {
        let style = Style::new().foreground(Color::Red);
        Some(ctx.bench("render_red_text", || {
            style.render("Hello");
        }))
    }
}

// Register and run
let mut registry = TestRegistry::new();
registry.register(RedTextTest);

let runner = TestRunner::new(registry, FixtureLoader::new("fixtures"));
let results = runner.run_all();
```

