## Purpose
The conformance harness itself needs comprehensive testing to ensure it works correctly before we trust it to validate our crate ports.

## Why This Matters
If the harness has bugs:
- False positives: Tests pass when they should fail
- False negatives: Tests fail when they should pass
- Incorrect diffs: Misleading error messages
- Statistical errors: Wrong benchmark conclusions

We must test the harness rigorously.

